## Features

- ðŸš€ **Intuitive syntax** for working with HTTP requests
- ðŸŒˆ **Beautiful colored output** with syntax highlighting
- ðŸ’¡ **Automatic content type detection** (JSON, XML, HTML)
- ðŸ” **OpenAPI specification inspection** for convenient API work
- ðŸ”„ **Curl command generation** for compatibility
- ðŸ“ **Automatic data formatting** (JSON, XML, HTML, Markdown)
- ðŸŒ **Environment support** for working with different APIs
- ðŸ” **Save and reuse** headers and tokens
- ðŸ’¾ **Save responses** to files
- ðŸ§° **Full support** for all HTTP methods
- ðŸŒ **WebSocket connections** for bidirectional communication
- ðŸ“Š **GraphQL requests** for working with GraphQL APIs
- ðŸ“œ **Request history** for reuse and analysis
- âš¡ **Parallel request execution** for improved performance

## Why Talkie?

Talkie combines the best of both worlds: the simplicity of HTTPie and the power of curl, while adding features that neither offers out of the box.

**When to choose Talkie over HTTPie:**
- You need **GraphQL** â€” Talkie has a dedicated `graphql` command with query files and variables
- You work with **WebSocket** â€” built-in `ws` command, no extra tools
- You explore **OpenAPI** specs â€” inspect endpoints, schemas, and generate examples
- You run **parallel requests** â€” batch API calls with configurable concurrency
- You want **searchable history** â€” find, repeat, and export past requests

**When to choose Talkie over curl:**
- You prefer **human-friendly syntax** â€” `talkie post /users name=John` instead of `-d '{"name":"John"}'`
- You want **colored, formatted output** â€” JSON/XML/HTML with syntax highlighting
- You need **environments** â€” switch between dev/staging/prod with one config
- You don't want to remember curl flags â€” intuitive `-H`, `-q`, `-o` options

### Unique Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **GraphQL** | Native `talkie graphql` with query files, variables, and introspection |
| **WebSocket** | `talkie ws` for real-time connections, no separate client needed |
| **OpenAPI** | Inspect specs, list endpoints, generate request examples |
| **Parallel requests** | `talkie parallel` for batch execution with concurrency control |
| **Request history** | Search, repeat, export/import â€” full audit trail of your API work |

